{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.9",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 9,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 9",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 9 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:2",
      "text": "“ Truly I know that it is so, but how can man be just with God?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:3",
      "text": "If he is pleased to contend with him, he can ’t answer him one time in a thousand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:4",
      "text": "God is wise in heart, and mighty in strength. Who has hardened himself against him and prospered?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:5",
      "text": "He removes the mountains, and they don’t know it, when he overturns them in his anger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:6",
      "text": "He shakes the earth out of its place. Its pillars tremble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:7",
      "text": "He commands the sun and it doesn’t rise, and seals up the stars.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:8",
      "text": "He alone stretches out the heavens, and treads on the waves of the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:9",
      "text": "He makes the Bear, Orion, and the Pleiades, and the rooms of the south.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:10",
      "text": "He does great things past finding out; yes, marvelous things without number.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:11",
      "text": "Behold, he goes by me, and I don’t see him. He passes on also, but I don’t perceive him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:12",
      "text": "Behold, he snatches away. Who can hinder him? Who will ask him, ‘ What are you doing?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:13",
      "text": "“ God will not withdraw his anger. The helpers of Rahab stoop under him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:14",
      "text": "How much less will I answer him, and choose my words to argue with him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:15",
      "text": "Though I were righteous, yet I wouldn’t answer him. I would make supplication to my judge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:16",
      "text": "If I had called, and he had answered me, yet I wouldn’t believe that he listened to my voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:17",
      "text": "For he breaks me with a storm, and multiplies my wounds without cause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:18",
      "text": "He will not allow me to catch my breath, but fills me with bitterness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:19",
      "text": "If it is a matter of strength, behold, he is mighty! If of justice, ‘ Who,’ says he, ‘ will summon me?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:20",
      "text": "Though I am righteous, my own mouth will condemn me. Though I am blameless, it will prove me perverse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:21",
      "text": "I am blameless. I don’t respect myself. I despise my life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:22",
      "text": "“ It is all the same. Therefore I say he destroys the blameless and the wicked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:23",
      "text": "If the scourge kills suddenly, he will mock at the trial of the innocent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:24",
      "text": "The earth is given into the hand of the wicked. He covers the faces of its judges. If not he, then who is it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:25",
      "text": "“ Now my days are swifter than a runner. They flee away. They see no good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:26",
      "text": "They have passed away as the swift ships, as the eagle that swoops on the prey.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:27",
      "text": "If I say, ‘ I will forget my complaint, I will put off my sad face, and cheer up,’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:28",
      "text": "I am afraid of all my sorrows. I know that you will not hold me innocent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:29",
      "text": "I will be condemned. Why then do I labor in vain?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:30",
      "text": "If I wash myself with snow, and cleanse my hands with lye,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:31",
      "text": "yet you will plunge me in the ditch. My own clothes will abhor me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:32",
      "text": "For he is not a man, as I am, that I should answer him, that we should come together in judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:33",
      "text": "There is no umpire between us, that might lay his hand on us both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:34",
      "text": "Let him take his rod away from me. Let his terror not make me afraid;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.9.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:35",
      "text": "then I would speak, and not fear him, for I am not so in myself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
